{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> μῆλον</b>, τό, <br /> <br /><Level1><b>__B</b></Level1><i>Doric dialect</i> and <i>Aeolic dialect</i> <b>μᾶλον</b>, <b>apple</b> or (generally) any <b>treefruit</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 9.542, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 7.120, 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 215, 335 (whereas in [prev. author] “Op.” only μῆλον (A) is found), 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.195, 2.92, 7.41; χνοῦς ὥσπερ μήλοισιν ἐπήνθει 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 978; χρύσια μ. 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 29.37 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; μ. ἄγριον <b>crab, Pyrus acerba</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Dioscorides (Dioscurides) Medicus 1.115.4\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; μ. Ἀρμενιακόν <b>apricot, Prunus armeniaca</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 1.115.5, 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 6.594 (μ. ἐαρινά “PCair.Zen.” 33.13 (3rd c.BC))\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; μ. Ἠπειρωτικόν <b>roseapple</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Dioscorides (Dioscurides) Medicus 1.115.4\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; μ. Κυδώνιον <b>quince</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ διαίτης” 2.55, 1st c.AD: Dioscorides (Dioscurides) Medicus 1.115.1, 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 6.563, “SIG” 1171.15 (from Lebena)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μ. Μηδικόν <b>citron, Citrus medica</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Dioscorides (Dioscurides) Medicus 1.115.5 (μ. κίτριον 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 12.77)\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; μ. Περσικόν <b>peach, Prunus persica</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 6.592; τῶν Ποντικῶν ἐκείνων ἂ καλοῦσι μῆλα, of a kind of gourd, [prev. work]563. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__B.2</b></Level3> <b>seed-vessel</b> of the rose, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 6.6.6. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>plural</i>, <i>metaphorically</i>, of a <b>girl's breasts</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 155, “Ec.” 903, 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 27.50. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__B.II.2</b></Level3> <b>cheeks,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" PPetr. 3.p.2, +others (3rd c.BC), “Anthologia Graeca” 9.556 (1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Zonas Epigrammaticus), 2nd c.AD: Rufus Medicus “περὶ ὀνομασίας” 46, 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Im.” 6, “Arch.Papyrus” 4.271 (3rd c.AD): in _sing._, μ. ἀριστερόν “BGU” 998.4 (2nd c.BC), etc.: but in 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 14.38, τὰ σὰ δάκρυα μᾶλα ῥέοντι\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>] thy tears run <b>like apples</b>, i.e. <b>big round tears and sweet withal.</b> <br /><Level3><b>__B.II.3</b></Level3> <b>swellings under the eye</b>, 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus see at {κύλα}. <br /><Level3><b>__B.II.4</b></Level3> <b>tonsils</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Rufus Medicus “περὶ ὀνομασίας” 64. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__B.II.5</b></Level3> <b>cups shaped like apples,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Inscriptiones Graecae 11(2).161 B 41, +others (Delos, 3rd c.BC)\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]. (Cf. Latin <i>mālum</i>, perhaps borrowed from Gr.)","strongNumber":"G8316","accentedUnicode":"μῆλον","shortDef":"cheeks; apple","mediumDef":"cheeks; apple","stepGloss":"cheeks","stepTransliteration":"mēlon","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}